docs.abstract: Can money buy happiness? A new study reveals that wealth gave people satisfaction and independence, but it also gave them a greater sense of responsibility.
docs.snippet: Can money buy happiness? A new study reveals that wealth gave people satisfaction and independence, but it also gave them a greater sense of responsibility.
docs.lead_paragraph: So much for that old saw that money can’t buy happiness. A new survey of people who have built significant wealth on their own found that money has actually bought them a lot of happiness.

headline.main: Balancing the Benefit and the Burden of Wealth
headline.print_headline: Did Money Buy Them Happiness? Yes. Regrets? Those, Too.

docs.abstract: The automaker, which was humbled after falsifying emissions data, still has work to do to protect potential whistle-blowers, according to its U.S. monitor.
docs.snippet: The automaker, which was humbled after falsifying emissions data, still has work to do to protect potential whistle-blowers, according to its U.S. monitor.
docs.lead_paragraph: WOLFSBURG, Germany — Nearly three years after Volkswagen admitted to a vast emissions cheating scheme, the company has only just begun to take steps necessary to prevent future scandals.

headline.main: Volkswagen’s Effort to Stop Scandals Needs More Work, Report Says
headline.print_headline: VW Has Miles to Go on Reforms, Report Finds
